HEADWORD: Wreck-master
<hw>Wreck"-mas`ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person
appointed by law to take charge of goods, etc., thrown on shore after a
shipwreck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

